RethinkDB in Production?
text:
Figuring out if a concept has legs and need to pick a datastore.

Using a single machine to start, à la hetzner. Will scale to cloud if needed.

RethinkDB sells as a real-time db, but realtime isn't necessarily my goal. Easy scaling, securing, backup, and administration are atop my desires. RethinkDB marketing material sells those use cases well.

Anyone else here running RethinkDB in production? I'd love to hear real-world stories, good and bad. Looking for potential drawbacks and any other feedback from the community.
